<taxonomicName box="[713,789,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amana">
<emphasis box="[713,789,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">amana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but its eyes are located farther forward on the head and there is no dense, longitudinal striolate ground sculpture between the eyes. See notes under 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1310,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schoutedeni">
